        <hl1>THE MARKETS: CURRENCIES</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Euro continues to rise on expectations that US economic growth will slow to be more in line with that of euro zone; in New York trading, euro settles at 84.14 cents, up from 84.03 cents; graph; chart (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>EURO RISES. The euro continued to rise on expectations that United States economic growth will slow to be more in line with that of the euro zone. In New York, the euro settled at 84.14 cents, up from 84.03 cents on Friday.</p>
      </block>
